codes.code: argmax 'Given a list of Latin sentences with words that have missing endings marked with the character ~, predict the missing endings based on the context. Provide the answer only. 1. Unde venit lūx lūnae? ... Choose from this set of possible answers [ lūx lūnae ā sōle venit, pars lūnae tantum sōle illūstrātur, is diēs dīcitur nōnae Aprīlēs, mēnse Iūniō diēs longissimī sunt, sunt aestās, hiems, vēr, autumnus, annus ā mēnse Iānuāriō incipit, ā Decembrī incipit hiems, mēnsis frīgidissimus est Iānuārius, ... quia aestās tempus calidissimum est, autumnō folia dē arboribus cadunt, vēre arborēs novīs foliīs ōrnantur, diēs brevissimus est ante diem octāvum kalendās Iānuāriās] [ANSWER]' from 'openai/text-davinci-002' where ANSWER in [ 'lūx lūnae ā sōle venit', 'pars lūnae tantum sōle illūstrātur', 'is diēs dīcitur 'nōnae Aprīlēs'', 'mēnse Iūniō diēs longissimī sunt', 'sunt aestās, hiems, vēr, autumnus', 'annus ā mēnse Iānuāriō incipit', 'ā Decembrī incipit hiems', 'mēnsis frīgidissimus est Iānuārius', '... quia aestās tempus calidissimum est', 'autumnō folia dē arboribus cadunt', 'vēre arborēs novīs foliīs ōrnantur', 'diēs brevissimus est ante diem octāvum kalendās Iānuāriās']
